The paper deals with covert communication in wireless networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and security (cs.CR). The use of multiple antennas by the adversary is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests the sub-category of networked systems (cs.NI) and multimedia (cs.MM) may also be relevant. Finally, the paper considers delay constraints, which could fall under the sub-category of control systems (cs.SY).
